          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The default ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSConnection",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object uses a single ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSPort",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object for both receiving and sending and is useful only for vending an object; use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsconnection/1478012-rootobject",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsconnection/1478102-registername",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " methods to do this.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "1680099",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Special Considerations",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The singleton method of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSConnection",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " has been deprecated. It was difficult to ensure that the shared connection wasnâ€™t being used by other operations on the thread on which the default connection was requested. Using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[NSConnection new]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " ensures that you get a unique connection object, preventing such collisions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
